This paper discusses the privacy of individuals in the context of data anonymization, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to attack anonymized data, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of databases to store and manage data, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of these attacks on population privacy, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
